definition: Nozdrzec is a village in Brzozów County, Subcarpathian Voivodeship, in south-eastern Poland. It is the seat of the gmina called Gmina Nozdrzec. It lies approximately 17 kilometres north-east of Brzozów and 32 km south-east of the regional capital Rzeszów. The village has a population of 1,300.
Çələbixan is a village and the least populous municipality in the Shaki Rayon of Azerbaijan. It has a population of 223. The municipality consists of the villages of Çələbixan, Qızılarx, and Kosalı.

Anton Anreith was a sculptor and woodcarver from Riegel near Freiburg in Breisgau, Baden, Germany. He is known for numerous sculptural embellishments that adorn buildings in the Cape region of South Africa, thought to represent the crowning achievement of the Cape Baroque style.

Bert Mather Carr was an American football player. He played college football at the guard and center positions for Adrian College in 1890 and for the University of Michigan from 1894 to 1896. In September 1896, the Chicago Daily Tribune called him "the best center in the West." In 1902, he was selected as the greatest guard in the history of the Michigan football program. He later worked as a medical doctor in Cedar Springs, Michigan.
